FBIS3-13667 "drnes053_n_94003" FBIS-NES-94-053 Document Type:Daily Report 17 Mar 1994 LEBANON Lebanese Forces Members Named in Assault Case NC1703183994 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1715 GMT 17 Mar 94 NC1703183994 Beirut Voice of Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] The Public Relations Department of the General Directorate of the Internal Security Forces issued the following statement today: Subsequent to an earlier statement by the General Directorate of the Internal Security Forces about the assault on Monsignor Ilyas al-Habr in Sayyidat al-Intiqal [Our Lady of the Assumption] Church, the Greek Catholic sect's church in al-Ashrafiyah, this is to report that it just so happens that the two arrested suspects Faris Philip al-Hajj, born in Harat Hurayk in 1950, currently residing in [place-name indistinct]; and Nabil Ptikoyan, born in al-Hadath in 1965 and currently resident of al-Jummayzah, are Lebanese Forces members. They constituted a two-man [word indistinct] in al-Shahruri Barracks in al-Ashrafiyah. Investigations continue. A former statement by the directorate announced that Muhammad al-Hajj 'Ali, born in 1971 and currently resident of Tariq al-Jadidah was also involved in the incident and indeed is owner of the vehicle used in the assault.
